-- BTG Adds Petrobras, Cuts Vale in November Stock Ideas Portfolio
-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 2010-11-01T09:38:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/btg-pactual-adds-petrobras-cuts-vale-in-november-10-stock-ideas-portfolio.html
Petroleo Brasileiro SA  was added to
Banco BTG Pactual SA’s “10 Stock Ideas for the Month”
portfolio for the first time this year after its  voting shares 
fell and it boosted production at the Tupi pilot project.  Vale SA ’s weight in the Brazilian stock portfolio was cut
to 15 percent and real-estate companies PDG Realty SA
Empreendimentos e Participacoes and Even Construtora e
Incorporadora SA were together cut to 10 percent to make room
for Petrobras, according to a BTG Pactual report dated today.
Petrobras makes up 20 percent of the portfolio.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA was added to the November
stock ideas portfolio, replacing Empresa Brasileira de
Aeronautica SA, according to the report by  Carlos Sequeira ,
 Antonio Junqueira  and  Bernardo Miranda .  To contact the reporter on this story:
